{"timestamp": "2025-12-12 09:55:13.026251", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: **Summary of the ping test**\\n\\nAll 64 PCs were able to ping both the “gateway” PC\\u202f3‑1 (10.3.1.2) and the “core” PC\\u202f1‑0 (10.1.0.2).  \\nFor every test the following was observed:\\n\\n| Destination | Packets sent | Packets received | Packet loss | Avg latency (ms) |\\n|-------------|--------------|------------------|-------------|------------------|\\n| PC\\u202f3‑1      | 2            | 2                | 0\\u202f%         | 1.4\\u202f–\\u202f5.3\\u202fms     |\\n| PC\\u202f1‑0      | 2            | 2                | 0\\u202f%         | 1.2\\u202f–\\u202f5.7\\u202fms     |\\n\\n* **No packet loss** – every ping returned two replies.  \\n* **Low latency** – all round‑trip times are well below 10\\u202fms, the highest being ~5.7\\u202fms for a few nodes.  \\n* **Consistent routing** – every node can reach both the gateway and the core router, indicating that the routing tables and forwarding rules are correctly installed.\\n\\n**Interpretation**\\n\\nThe network is fully functional.  \\n* All sub‑nets are reachable from each other.  \\n* The routing between the three LAN segments (10.1.0.0/24, 10.2.0.0/24, 10.3.0.0/24) is working as expected.  \\n* The small variations in latency are normal for a virtualised environment and do not indicate any bottleneck or mis‑configuration.\\n\\n**Conclusion**\\n\\nThe ping results confirm that the network connectivity is healthy: every host can reach the gateway and the core router with no packet loss and acceptable latency. No further troubleshooting is required at this time., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='a710a4c0-06e3-4309-ac23-961cb39ed79b'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "not_implemented", "id": ["langchain_ollama", "chat_models", "ChatOllama"], "repr": "ChatOllama(model='gpt-oss:20b', validate_model_on_init=True